### SmartAid REST tests — Campaign Enrollment (admin only)
### This file creates its own fresh campaign so it doesn't depend on other
### test files. It enrolls beneficiaries, tests the budget cap, then closes
### the campaign and verifies frozen-state errors.

@host = http://localhost:3000

### Login as admin
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@smartaid.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Create a fresh draft campaign with budget 600
# @name createCampaign
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Enrollment REST Test",
  "location": "Mogadishu",
  "start_date": "2026-09-01",
  "end_date": "2026-09-30",
  "budget": 600
}

### 1) GET enrollments for campaign with none yet
# Expected: 200, { enrollments: [] }
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 2) GET enrollments for non-existent campaign
# Expected: 404
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns/9999/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 3) Enroll beneficiary id=1 with 300
# Expected: 201, remaining_balance == allocated_balance == 300
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "beneficiary_id": 1,
  "allocated_balance": 300
}

### 4) Try to enroll beneficiary id=1 AGAIN
# Expected: 409 "already enrolled"
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "beneficiary_id": 1,
  "allocated_balance": 50
}

### 5) Enroll beneficiary id=2 with 400 — would exceed budget (300+400=700 > 600)
# Expected: 409 with details.available = 300
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "beneficiary_id": 2,
  "allocated_balance": 400
}

### 6) Enroll beneficiary id=2 with exact remaining 300 (300+300=600)
# Expected: 201
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "beneficiary_id": 2,
  "allocated_balance": 300
}

### 7) Enroll non-existent beneficiary
# Expected: 404
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "beneficiary_id": 9999,
  "allocated_balance": 50
}

### 8) Bad allocation amount
# Expected: 400
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "beneficiary_id": 1,
  "allocated_balance": 0
}

### 9) Missing fields
# Expected: 400
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 10) GET enrollments now (should show 2 with beneficiary names)
# Expected: 200, enrollments array with 2 items
GET {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### 11) PUT update beneficiary id=1 allocation from 300 -> 250
# Expected: 200, allocated=250, remaining=250 (spent was 0, delta -50)
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries/1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "allocated_balance": 250
}

### 12) PUT update beneficiary id=1 from 250 -> 400 — total would be 700 > 600
# Expected: 409 with details
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries/1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "allocated_balance": 400
}

### 13) PUT non-existent enrollment
# Expected: 404
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries/9999
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "allocated_balance": 100
}

### 14) PUT bad allocated value
# Expected: 400
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries/1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "allocated_balance": -5
}

### 15) Close the campaign (refund: 250+300 = 550 back to ngo_account)
# Expected: 200, refunded = 550
# Check pgAdmin afterwards: this campaign's enrollment rows have remaining_balance = 0
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

### 16) Now close it
# Expected: 200, refunded = 550 since none was spent
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/status
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "closed"
}

### 17) Try to enroll into a closed campaign
# Expected: 409
POST {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "beneficiary_id": 1,
  "allocated_balance": 50
}

### 18) Try to update an allocation on a closed campaign
# Expected: 409
PUT {{host}}/api/campaigns/{{createCampaign.response.body.data.id}}/beneficiaries/1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.data.token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "allocated_balance": 100
}
